.TH venv "1" "February 2026" "SMI Toolset 0.100.0" "SMI Python Command"
.SH NAME
venv \- Activate the local virtual environment in the current shell
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B . venv
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.B venv
is a small utility script to activate the local \fB./.venv\fR virtual environment.
It must be sourced (using the dot or source command) to affect the current shell session.
If the \fB./.venv\fR directory is not found, it prints an error and exits.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
To activate the virtual environment:
.IP
.B . venv
